§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A ❬(real) matrix polynomial❭ of ❬degree❭ $d$ is a function
    $p: 𝗥^{n × n} → 𝗥^{n × n}$ for which there exists a
    finite sequence $(c_0, c_1, …, c_{d-1}, c_d) ∈ 𝗥^{d+1}$
    satisfying,
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ p(A) = c_0 I + c_1 A^1 + c_2 A^2 + ⋯ + c_dA^d, ⦉
    ⦉
    for all $A ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$. ⦉
⦉

